social_posts.post_text: Hey friends & family! I’m super excited to invite all of you to this amazing weekend event where I’ll be doing a live free cooking demo. You won’t want to miss Kroger’s Magical Cookbook Experience featuring yours truly. Join us on Saturday, December 10th from 2PM – 3PM at the Hollywood West Fred Meyer, 3030 NE Weidler St. for a holiday celebration of food and family. I’ll be there cooking with my mom as my very special guest as we prepare some Pork and Cabbage Dumplings with fresh Kimchi that everyone will be able to sample. Hope to see you all there! @krogerco @fredmeyerstores #MagicalCookbook #Kroger

[Portland, OR] @hanoakpdx 

Dining at @hanoakpdx was definitely a top highlight on our last Portland trip! It was such a fun and lively experience. Once you walk through the doors you automatically feel welcomed. The restaurant has a cozy, cute and intimate vibe! The interior is well decorated and the set up makes you feel right at home. On the same note, the staff makes you feel valued and treats you like family 😀.

We got to try their seasonal menu which is the Gimbap Party! The Gimbap party is an awesome experience because you get to create your own gimbap. Everything was made fresh and tasted amazing. The Bulgogi and Koji Cured Coppa were so tender and packed with divine flavors. Also, you’re able to reorder your favorite dishes… so there’s no excuse for you to not leave full. 

We can’t wait to go to Han Oak in the near future! Chef @petecho knows how to blend good food with great vibes! Also, we will be back for some Karaoke lol! Book your reservations right away to @hanoakpdx because they go by pretty quickly! When you’re there make sure you try their fantastic cocktails..our favorite is the Umami Mommie 👌🏼. Let us know if you been to Han Oak or if you plan on going in the future. Get your Grub on 🍽️!

Celebrating Korean American Heritage 🇰🇷🇺🇸

Saturday, Jan. 13 is Korean American Heritage Day. Multnomah County celebrated Korean American heritage during today’s public board meeting with storytelling from Korean American leaders. 

Afterwards @hanoakpdx owners Peter Cho and Sun Young Park served Korean cuisine, including kimchi and duck mandu guk (Korean rice cake and dumpling soup)!

WHEN THEY SAY SNOW AND ICE IS COMING ❄️ WE LISTEN AND SO HAN OAK WILL BE CLOSED FOR SERVICE SATURDAY 1/13 AND WE SUGGEST EATING PIZZA, STAYING WARM AND SAFE 🍕

📷 @kari_myoung
